Wiki Search project

User Story: I can search Wikipedia entries in a search box and see the resulting Wikipedia entries.
User Story: I can click a button to see a random Wikipedia entry.

Hint #1: Here's a URL you can use to get a random Wikipedia article: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:Random.
Hint #2: Here's an entry on using Wikipedia's API: http://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/API:Main_page.
Hint #3: Use this link to experiment with Wikipedia's API: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:ApiSandbox#action=query&titles=Main%20Page&prop=revisions&rvprop=content&format=jsonfm


The search text shall be processed to form the WikiMedia API call.

The search results, returned by the WikiMedia API, should be shown with a title and short text description.
The title should be a hyperlink to the Wikipedia entry which opens in a new browser tab.
The results list is cleared when a new search is made or when the search field is cleared.

https://en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=query&format=json&list=search&titles=&srsearch=samuel+pepys

/w/api.php?action=query&format=json&prop=&list=search&meta=&titles=&srsearch=samuel+pepys&srnamespace=0&srwhat=text&srinfo=totalhits%7Csuggestion%7Crewrittenquery

/w/api.php?action=query&format=json&prop=extracts&titles=Samuel+Pepys%7CThe+Private+Life+of+Samuel+Pepys%7CSaye&exlimit=10&exintro=1&explaintext=1